Document: AudioEffectRecord
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectrecord.rst
Summary: Specifies the audio format for recording samples

Format format = 1
- void set_format(value: Format)
- Format get_format()

Specifies the format in which the sample will be recorded. The format property determines the audio encoding type used for recording, with a default value of 1. The set_format method allows changing the format, and get_format retrieves the current format setting. The available format options are defined in the AudioStreamWAV_Format enum.
---CHUNK---
Document: AudioEffectRecord
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectrecord.rst
Summary: Methods for managing audio recording functionality, including starting/stopping recording and retrieving recorded samples.

Method: get_recording() → AudioStreamWAV. Returns the recorded sample.
Method: is_recording_active() → bool. Returns whether the recording is active or not.
Method: set_recording_active(record: bool) → void. If true, the sound will be recorded. Note: Restarting the recording will remove the previously recorded sample.